# HandsOff reporting obligations (Rule 37)

**Canonical procedure:** `.cursor/skills/hands-off-playwright-report/SKILL.md`  
**Step order:** `.cursor/commands/hands-off.md`  
**Machine report:** `.cursor/rules/workflows/playwright_detailed_reporting.mdc` (DPR.0)

## Exit criteria (summary)

| Gate | Requirement |
|------|-------------|
| Step 3 | TC `.md` on disk; **Backend always**; **Frontend when TC-FRONTEND scope** includes it |
| Step 3.5 | **test-case-quality-validator** ≥80/100; max 3; **BLOCK** if still failing |
| Step 4 | Spec via **energo-ts-test**; 1:1 TC coverage; Rule 40/41 |
| Step 4.5 | **playwright-test-validator** pass; max 3; **BLOCK** before run |
| Step 6–7 | `{JIRA_KEY}.md` + optional `playwright-report-detailed.md`; Slack 3-block + **file uploads** Tester + #ai-report only |

## Common failures (do not repeat)

- TC "created" but files missing on disk
- Spec count ≠ TC count; ad-hoc getToken instead of fixtures
- Long Slack body instead of file uploads
- Skipping Step 3.5 or 4.5

